1
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:11,078
I’d like to propose

2
00:00:11,442 --> 00:00:13,333
that Petchprakai try adjusting its promotion.

3
00:00:13,466 --> 00:00:16,166
If we promote it as
“vertical Likay,”

4
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,933
it should be much more interesting.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,266
Do you think people will like our pilot?

6
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:22,700
Did you put up a notice for Guy’s series?

7
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:24,566
We’re on Guy’s team.

8
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:25,604
You got this!

9
00:00:25,877 --> 00:00:27,539
I like dogs too.

10
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:29,500
Especially big ones.

11
00:00:29,966 --> 00:00:31,733
We’ll get through this together.

12
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:36,866
It’s all gone.

13
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,500
Besides the clothes, is anything else missing?

14
00:00:39,666 --> 00:00:40,666
The jewelry too.

15
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,533
Those were Father and Mother’s heirlooms.

16
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,000
No way.

17
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,933
Could it be those three?

18
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,800
Have they been acting strange lately?

19
00:00:51,066 --> 00:00:52,466
They’ve been glued to their phones lately.

20
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:53,900
More than anything else.

21
00:01:14,666 --> 00:01:15,693
You guys…

22
00:01:16,011 --> 00:01:18,018
Are you sure you want to do this now?

23
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,466
They just split up.

24
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,133
Now is the best time.

25
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,333
They just called me.

26
00:01:25,933 --> 00:01:27,566
Saying if I don’t pay them back,

27
00:01:27,866 --> 00:01:29,200
they’ll come after us here.

28
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,200
I won’t risk anyone getting into trouble.

29
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:34,700
This is our only chance to get away.

30
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:38,376
What about these costumes?

31
00:01:38,376 --> 00:01:39,775
Are you really sure

32
00:01:40,275 --> 00:01:41,405
you want to take them?

33
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,366
At first, I wasn’t sure,

34
00:01:44,566 --> 00:01:47,060
but this evening I saw P’Phet and P’Ploy

35
00:01:47,060 --> 00:01:48,800
get by without costumes.

36
00:01:49,333 --> 00:01:51,066
But we don’t have any Likay costumes.

37
00:01:52,066 --> 00:01:53,333
No jobs, no money.

38
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:57,300
If we don’t go now, they’ll—

39
00:01:58,600 --> 00:01:59,889
Think about it.

40
00:02:00,207 --> 00:02:02,537
The whole house is chaotic right now.

41
00:02:02,764 --> 00:02:04,211
No one will pay attention to us.

42
00:02:04,529 --> 00:02:07,728
This is the only time we can leave

43
00:02:07,955 --> 00:02:09,208
without getting caught.

44
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:17,866
Thank you for everything.

45
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:21,133
And I’m sorry for doing this.

46
00:02:28,966 --> 00:02:30,369
They might not understand,

47
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:32,489
but if we stay,

48
00:02:33,671 --> 00:02:34,949
they’ll definitely come after us.

49
00:02:35,995 --> 00:02:38,715
P’Phet shouldn’t have to take the blame
for what we did.

50
00:02:42,166 --> 00:02:43,590
I’m sorry, P’Phet.

51
00:02:44,999 --> 00:02:46,026
P’Ploy…

52
00:02:46,662 --> 00:02:47,625
Pleng…

53
00:02:47,989 --> 00:02:48,851
Guy…

54
00:02:49,487 --> 00:02:50,740
If I ever have money,

55
00:02:51,786 --> 00:02:52,990
I’ll come back and repay everything.

56
00:02:53,808 --> 00:02:54,620
Every baht.

57
00:02:54,938 --> 00:02:55,974
Every costume.

58
00:02:56,929 --> 00:02:58,296
Everything.

59
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,800
Let’s go.

60
00:03:10,566 --> 00:03:11,600
Is everyone here?

61
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:13,800
I want to go over what’s missing.

62
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,100
Ping, Pong, and Chae aren’t here.

63
00:03:16,466 --> 00:03:18,000
I saw them go shower a while ago.

64
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:18,966
They’re still not back.

65
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:22,000
Wait a second.

66
00:03:23,366 --> 00:03:26,500
I just saw the bathroom was empty.

67
00:03:26,866 --> 00:03:29,100
This feels strange. I’ll go check on them.

68
00:03:29,866 --> 00:03:30,666
I’ll go with you.

69
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:35,212
Let’s go.

70
00:03:35,803 --> 00:03:36,957
Now’s the time.

71
00:05:08,966 --> 00:05:10,462
Thank you for everything.

72
00:05:11,553 --> 00:05:13,402
And I’m sorry for doing this.

73
00:05:27,700 --> 00:05:29,300
You’re still awake, P’Phet?

74
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,666
Why do you look so pale?

75
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,180
Hey—

76
00:05:46,135 --> 00:05:47,162
The things…

77
00:05:47,162 --> 00:05:48,488
Where did everything go, P’Phet?

78
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,430
It’s not just the things.

79
00:05:53,839 --> 00:05:55,902
It’s all the memories of this house.

80
00:06:00,900 --> 00:06:03,133
Ping, Pong, and Chae have left our troupe, Ploy.

81
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,666
Then you should report it.

82
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:10,933
This isn’t a small matter anymore.

83
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,400
No.

84
00:06:15,966 --> 00:06:17,366
They’re our family.

85
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,933
We’ve been together for years.

86
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:28,800
I don’t want anyone going to jail.

87
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:29,733
This way.

88
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,300
Family?

89
00:06:32,733 --> 00:06:34,133
Look at what they did.

90
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:37,133
Is that what family does?

91
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:40,587
P’Phet…

92
00:06:40,996 --> 00:06:42,718
Your kindness

93
00:06:43,354 --> 00:06:46,129
might bring the whole troupe down.

94
00:06:49,166 --> 00:06:50,900
I believe there must be a reason

95
00:06:52,866 --> 00:06:54,600
that pushed them to do this.

96
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,233
So…

97
00:07:00,506 --> 00:07:02,206
what are you going to do next?

98
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,639
Then we have to let everyone know, Ploy,

99
00:07:10,230 --> 00:07:11,542
that the Petchprakai Troupe

100
00:07:11,769 --> 00:07:13,718
is not something anyone can mess with.

101
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,212
P’Phet…

102
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:19,723
What are you going to do?

103
00:07:20,496 --> 00:07:22,836
Don’t tell me you’re posting it on Facebook.

104
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:26,996
I’m not exposing anyone.

105
00:07:27,632 --> 00:07:30,312
I just want everyone to know that
our Petchprakai Troupe

106
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:33,402
is not something anyone can hurt
and walk away from.

107
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:35,692
P’Phet…

108
00:07:37,056 --> 00:07:39,175
Have you really thought this through?

109
00:07:40,366 --> 00:07:42,000
I didn’t mention anyone, Ploy.

110
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,266
I’m just posting what actually happened.

111
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,566
That we were robbed of what mattered most.

112
00:07:49,533 --> 00:07:51,000
And I want everyone to know

113
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,200
that no matter how many times we fall,

114
00:07:53,533 --> 00:07:55,100
we can always get back up.

115
00:08:06,828 --> 00:08:08,300
Anyone trying to hurt our troupe,
once we find them,

116
00:08:08,301 --> 00:08:09,328
we won’t let them get away with it.

117
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,700
This troupe is our home.

118
00:08:22,966 --> 00:08:24,133
Even if someone betrays us,

119
00:08:25,366 --> 00:08:26,933
I will protect it.

120
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:44,592
Hey…

121
00:08:45,819 --> 00:08:46,833
Are you awake?

122
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,000
Hey…

123
00:09:03,933 --> 00:09:04,733
Hey…

124
00:09:17,266 --> 00:09:18,742
I don’t know when it started,

125
00:09:21,788 --> 00:09:23,926
but my heart races when I look at you.

126
00:09:27,153 --> 00:09:28,043
At first,

127
00:09:28,361 --> 00:09:30,000
I thought I just liked you on TV.

128
00:09:32,066 --> 00:09:33,800
But being this close,

129
00:09:36,766 --> 00:09:37,966
it’s not just that anymore.

130
00:09:49,366 --> 00:09:50,779
If you like me that much,

131
00:09:52,188 --> 00:09:53,573
then don’t run away.

132
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,366
Was I sleep-talking?

133
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,200
So you finally said it.

134
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,841
This morning,

135
00:11:16,841 --> 00:11:18,766
it felt like someone woke me up.

136
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:23,133
Like they were saying something sweet.

137
00:11:24,133 --> 00:11:24,933
Crazy.

138
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:30,412
No, not really.

139
00:11:31,412 --> 00:11:33,318
Who would say something like that?

140
00:11:34,766 --> 00:11:36,146
But it’s strange…

141
00:11:36,146 --> 00:11:37,500
it sounded like you.

142
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:40,070
The tone was like someone

143
00:11:41,115 --> 00:11:43,038
who’s been secretly in love for a long time.

144
00:11:43,733 --> 00:11:44,733
Don’t say that.

145
00:11:47,133 --> 00:11:50,266
I just want to know if it’s true.

146
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:51,966
True…

147
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,155
or not?

148
00:12:00,666 --> 00:12:02,333
So this is how you tease me now?

149
00:12:03,366 --> 00:12:04,428
Then

150
00:12:04,973 --> 00:12:07,181
you owe me an answer.

151
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,333
Let’s eat.

152
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:15,300
Okay.

153
00:12:28,366 --> 00:12:29,287
Usually,

154
00:12:30,242 --> 00:12:32,905
Ping, Pong, and Chae would sit there

155
00:12:32,905 --> 00:12:33,900
making everyone laugh every morning.

156
00:12:33,966 --> 00:12:35,709
♪ Turn it into a bong ♪

157
00:12:35,709 --> 00:12:36,209
Hey—

158
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,350
But now…

159
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,601
it’s so quiet it feels empty.

160
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:45,066
It’s not just the laughter that’s gone,

161
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:50,466
it’s like the whole spirit of the troupe is gone too.

162
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:56,200
Even without them,

163
00:12:56,866 --> 00:12:58,466
we still have to keep going.

164
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:01,800
Hey—

165
00:13:04,482 --> 00:13:05,708
I went to look into it.

166
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:08,626
I asked everyone from the pork seller
to the fish seller.

167
00:13:08,626 --> 00:13:10,958
I questioned the whole market like it was a big case.

168
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:13,761
But no one has seen Ping, Pong, or Chae.

169
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:19,544
But one lady was acting nervous,
saying her bananas were gone.

170
00:13:19,544 --> 00:13:22,048
So I had to go full undercover.

171
00:13:22,048 --> 00:13:25,829
I helped her search for them from under the pan to behind the shop, and unbelievably,

172
00:13:26,284 --> 00:13:27,343
and ended up with fried bananas.

173
00:13:27,752 --> 00:13:30,582
I failed the case—I couldn’t find them.

174
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:41,494
So Detective Pleng Chai

175
00:13:41,721 --> 00:13:42,915
closed the case.

176
00:13:43,188 --> 00:13:44,229
But—

177
00:13:44,502 --> 00:13:46,239
it turned into a banana case.

178
00:13:46,366 --> 00:13:50,366
I tried to search for them.
I really tried , but I couldn’t find them.

179
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,966
So I ended up helping her find bananas instead.

180
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:53,966
Fried bananas.

181
00:13:54,066 --> 00:13:54,866
Fried bananas.

182
00:13:57,466 --> 00:13:58,431
P’Phet…

183
00:13:59,295 --> 00:14:01,147
I think Pleng’s got something.

184
00:14:01,147 --> 00:14:03,811
Even when he jokes, it’s funny.

185
00:14:03,811 --> 00:14:06,700
It feels natural too—interesting, right?

186
00:14:07,133 --> 00:14:08,352
Yeah, true.

187
00:14:08,716 --> 00:14:10,533
We’re missing a comedian now, right?

188
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:11,033
Yeah.

189
00:14:11,233 --> 00:14:13,687
Someone who can lighten the mood.

190
00:14:13,914 --> 00:14:15,527
And he’s standing right here.

191
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:19,964
Looks like our banana case detective

192
00:14:19,964 --> 00:14:21,866
should try something new.

193
00:14:23,566 --> 00:14:24,708
What do you mean?

194
00:14:24,935 --> 00:14:26,627
You want me to investigate someone?

195
00:14:27,266 --> 00:14:28,333
Banana Case Part Two?

196
00:14:28,566 --> 00:14:29,351
No.

197
00:14:29,351 --> 00:14:30,578
I want you

198
00:14:30,805 --> 00:14:33,027
to try being the comedian.

199
00:14:33,866 --> 00:14:35,023
Me?

200
00:14:35,023 --> 00:14:36,374
What do you want me to do?

201
00:14:36,374 --> 00:14:38,766
Stand there frying bananas on stage?

202
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,400
No.

203
00:14:40,466 --> 00:14:42,147
Not that far.

204
00:14:42,602 --> 00:14:45,321
I just think if you really try,

205
00:14:45,321 --> 00:14:48,466
you might make everyone laugh like
they did before.

206
00:14:49,266 --> 00:14:50,466
If everyone wants me to do it,

207
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,366
I’ll try frying bananas.

208
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:54,533
Not fried bananas.

209
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:56,200
(Phet Thae) It’s a “banana joke.”
(Ploy Ying) Ha! (Pleng Chai) Ha!

210
00:14:56,666 --> 00:14:57,600
It’s “eat bananas,” idiot.

211
00:14:57,827 --> 00:14:58,327
Ha!

212
00:14:58,566 --> 00:14:59,966
Wanna try some? Fresh out.

213
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,645
(Phet Thae) Yeah, I’m hungry.
(Pleng Chai) Ha!

214
00:15:02,281 --> 00:15:03,502
What is this?

215
00:15:11,766 --> 00:15:13,766
Hey, our new comedian.

216
00:15:15,866 --> 00:15:17,166
News travels fast.

217
00:15:18,266 --> 00:15:20,300
Figures, coming from the social police.

218
00:15:20,566 --> 00:15:21,366
Of course.

219
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:23,600
But please,

220
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:26,266
don’t call me that.

221
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,766
I’m not confident yet.

222
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,166
Here.

223
00:15:30,166 --> 00:15:31,066
Hey, hey—

224
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:33,966
add some sugar first.

225
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:41,100
Is it good?

226
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:44,300
It’s good.

227
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,500
Water—

228
00:15:49,133 --> 00:15:49,933
Here—

229
00:15:49,933 --> 00:15:50,733
Try this.

230
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:53,966
How do you choke on just bread like that?

231
00:15:56,966 --> 00:15:57,766
That was close.

232
00:15:57,933 --> 00:15:59,933
Not sure if you’re funny,

233
00:16:00,066 --> 00:16:02,533
but watching you eat bread already is.

234
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:06,066
You’re laughing too hard.

235
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:08,000
Ow—

236
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,500
Don’t stress.

237
00:16:09,666 --> 00:16:11,000
Don’t worry, okay?

238
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:15,300
You may not be as good as those three yet,

239
00:16:16,966 --> 00:16:18,012
but I think

240
00:16:19,421 --> 00:16:21,332
if you just be yourself,

241
00:16:22,332 --> 00:16:23,214
it’s already charming.

242
00:16:26,714 --> 00:16:28,525
Finish eating and go help P’Phet.

243
00:16:29,252 --> 00:16:31,400
Stop sitting around—give me that water.

244
00:16:32,166 --> 00:16:33,900
Okay, okay—go help P’Phet.

245
00:16:45,866 --> 00:16:46,666
Hey you—

246
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,800
You still say “I love you” so stiff.

247
00:16:50,766 --> 00:16:51,966
Look me in the eyes.

248
00:16:53,866 --> 00:16:54,666
Okay.

249
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:06,900
I…

250
00:17:11,066 --> 00:17:11,866
love you.

251
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,000
I love you.

252
00:17:13,166 --> 00:17:13,966
I love you.

253
00:17:26,133 --> 00:17:28,133
Got an answer yet?

254
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:30,700
What answer?

255
00:17:33,966 --> 00:17:35,066
That thing.

256
00:17:36,533 --> 00:17:37,333
That thing?

257
00:17:39,566 --> 00:17:40,666
What are you talking about?

258
00:17:42,566 --> 00:17:44,066
This is all we have right now.

259
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:45,800
Let’s keep practicing.

260
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:49,133
Okay.

261
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,900
I’ll leave it for now.

262
00:17:51,533 --> 00:17:53,066
I’ll come back for that answer.

263
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:56,410
You’re still not answering?

264
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:57,000
Hey—

265
00:17:58,133 --> 00:17:58,933
Practice.

266
00:17:59,133 --> 00:18:00,000
Come on.

267
00:18:01,133 --> 00:18:02,866
Where are you stuck? I’ll help.

268
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,966
Then try saying this line.

269
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:20,827
P’Phet,

270
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:25,670
our expenses this month
are higher than what we make.

271
00:18:26,666 --> 00:18:29,452
There are costume and equipment costs,

272
00:18:29,452 --> 00:18:32,335
stage, transport, and electricity too.

273
00:18:32,335 --> 00:18:34,856
If we don’t manage this properly,

274
00:18:35,083 --> 00:18:36,324
then soon

275
00:18:36,551 --> 00:18:38,690
we’ll all be exhausted.

276
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,466
I know it’s not easy,

277
00:18:43,533 --> 00:18:45,700
but we’ve come this far.

278
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,366
We can’t stop now.

279
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:50,900
We have to keep going.

280
00:18:51,566 --> 00:18:52,900
Not just for the work,

281
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:56,000
but so our troupe can keep standing.

282
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,000
We can’t carry this on our own anymore.

283
00:19:01,933 --> 00:19:04,000
I think we need more help.

284
00:19:04,866 --> 00:19:05,666
Yeah.

285
00:19:07,066 --> 00:19:08,106
I think so too.

286
00:19:09,197 --> 00:19:12,248
If someone could handle the work side,

287
00:19:12,521 --> 00:19:14,041
find sponsors,

288
00:19:14,314 --> 00:19:18,128
or help promote us more,

289
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,425
maybe…

290
00:19:23,107 --> 00:19:25,055
Mr. Tohr might be able to help us.

291
00:19:25,966 --> 00:19:27,066
Mr. Tohr?

292
00:19:27,866 --> 00:19:28,666
The other day,

293
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:30,333
I saw someone from the Payusin troupe

294
00:19:30,466 --> 00:19:31,766
posting complaints,

295
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,095
saying he’s very strict about money

296
00:19:33,095 --> 00:19:34,057
comment: booking agents these days are
extremely tough about money.

297
00:19:34,057 --> 00:19:35,225
I get that precision matters,
but this is harsh—really harsh.

298
00:19:35,225 --> 00:19:35,725
And there are many conditions.

299
00:19:35,725 --> 00:19:36,225
It’s a shame the troupe
hasn’t shown their full potential

300
00:19:36,225 --> 00:19:36,725
because someone controls everything.

301
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:39,040
When it comes to selling each job,

302
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,330
everything has to go through him.

303
00:19:40,330 --> 00:19:44,400
And the other day,
I heard him complain about it myself.

304
00:19:45,466 --> 00:19:47,396
You know how we feel.

305
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:50,073
But right now, what I’m most afraid of

306
00:19:50,073 --> 00:19:53,966
is that our troupe won’t make it.

307
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:58,160
Everyone has already given it their all.

308
00:19:58,660 --> 00:20:01,274
Both acting and performing on stage.

309
00:20:01,274 --> 00:20:05,469
If no one comes in to help with the work side,

310
00:20:05,469 --> 00:20:09,078
Ploy and I won’t have the energy left to rehearse

311
00:20:09,578 --> 00:20:11,536
or take care of everyone like before.

312
00:20:16,066 --> 00:20:18,526
Maybe having Mr. Tohr step in

313
00:20:18,526 --> 00:20:21,742
can help us get through this.

314
00:20:22,287 --> 00:20:23,710
At least,

315
00:20:24,710 --> 00:20:26,332
it would keep the troupe going.

316
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:31,388
So…

317
00:20:32,161 --> 00:20:34,066
I’ll try calling Mr. Tohr.

318
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,666
If Guy were here right now,

319
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:48,700
he’d definitely think the same as me.

320
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:57,032
I’ll head back first.

321
00:20:57,032 --> 00:20:59,766
Please take care of the coffee sponsor for my troupe.

322
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,191
Of course. I’ll handle it.

323
00:21:02,191 --> 00:21:02,966
Safe travels.

324
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:04,100
Okay.

325
00:21:08,766 --> 00:21:10,300
Oh, Phet Thae, Ploy Ying.

326
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:11,200
Hello, Mr. Tohr.

327
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,133
Hello.

328
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:14,246
Ploy and I

329
00:21:14,246 --> 00:21:17,000
I have something I’d like to ask
for your help with, sir.

330
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:19,600
What is it? Go ahead.

331
00:21:21,100 --> 00:21:21,696
Well…

332
00:21:21,969 --> 00:21:23,474
Right now, our troupe

333
00:21:23,474 --> 00:21:25,914
is having trouble competing for jobs, Mr. Tohr.

334
00:21:25,914 --> 00:21:29,439
So we’d like to ask for your help.

335
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:30,571
Sure.

336
00:21:30,571 --> 00:21:32,159
If it’s for the Petchprakai Troupe,

337
00:21:32,159 --> 00:21:33,300
I’m more than willing to help.

338
00:21:34,666 --> 00:21:35,914
Thank you very much.

339
00:21:35,914 --> 00:21:38,593
Um, about the commission,

340
00:21:38,866 --> 00:21:41,700
what percentage would you take?

341
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:43,100
Well…

342
00:21:43,533 --> 00:21:47,285
For others, I take fifteen to twenty percent.

343
00:21:47,921 --> 00:21:50,858
For you, I’ll start at ten.

344
00:21:50,858 --> 00:21:53,765
I’ve known you since you were young.

345
00:21:54,492 --> 00:21:56,669
We’ll help each other out.

346
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:01,133
I’ll start handling things from tomorrow.

347
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,400
This time, our troupe will rise again—
stronger than before.

348
00:22:05,266 --> 00:22:06,868
I’ll take care of everything.

349
00:22:06,868 --> 00:22:11,857
Sponsors, bookings, promotion,
PR—everything.

350
00:22:11,857 --> 00:22:13,398
The overall direction too.

351
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:16,105
This time, I want all of you

352
00:22:16,105 --> 00:22:18,200
to work like real professionals.

353
00:22:20,366 --> 00:22:21,445
Yes, Father.

354
00:22:21,445 --> 00:22:24,222
I promise, no matter what you plan,

355
00:22:24,222 --> 00:22:25,494
I’ll do my best.

356
00:22:25,494 --> 00:22:27,557
The Petchprakai Troupe

357
00:22:27,557 --> 00:22:29,766
will definitely stand on stage again.

358
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Good.

359
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:57,400
Stop, stop.

360
00:22:58,366 --> 00:22:59,053
Stop.

361
00:22:59,053 --> 00:22:59,900
That’s enough.

362
00:23:00,800 --> 00:23:02,133
What are you doing?

363
00:23:03,366 --> 00:23:05,441
This has no artistry at all.

364
00:23:06,396 --> 00:23:09,699
From now on, our Petchprakai Troupe

365
00:23:09,699 --> 00:23:12,556
won’t be just ordinary Likay,

366
00:23:12,556 --> 00:23:14,566
but a professional team.

367
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:17,486
Rehearsal starts at exactly 9 a.m.

368
00:23:17,804 --> 00:23:20,850
Lunch break is exactly 30 minutes.

369
00:23:21,259 --> 00:23:22,857
No more, no less.

370
00:23:22,857 --> 00:23:24,488
After rehearsal,

371
00:23:24,488 --> 00:23:26,467
no going out anywhere.

372
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:29,500
Put every piece of equipment away
don’t leave a single one out.

373
00:23:30,533 --> 00:23:32,100
This feels like military school.

374
00:23:33,366 --> 00:23:35,666
So no more evening market trips.

375
00:23:38,766 --> 00:23:41,263
If you don’t want to stay, don’t follow this.

376
00:23:41,263 --> 00:23:42,915
If you do want to stay,

377
00:23:44,142 --> 00:23:47,039
you still have today to choose.

378
00:23:47,584 --> 00:23:49,017
Tomorrow, you won’t.

379
00:23:49,727 --> 00:23:52,066
As for you, Pleng Chai,

380
00:23:52,666 --> 00:23:54,261
after university,

381
00:23:54,261 --> 00:23:57,725
come straight back to rehearse, not go play games.

382
00:23:57,725 --> 00:24:01,440
On weekends, come rehearse too.

383
00:24:01,758 --> 00:24:03,265
Let me tell you something.

384
00:24:03,992 --> 00:24:06,702
Being a Likay comedian isn’t easy.

385
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,674
Phet Thae.

386
00:24:13,856 --> 00:24:15,448
Keep the rehearsal going.

387
00:24:16,766 --> 00:24:17,733
Yes, Mr. Tohr.

388
00:24:23,733 --> 00:24:26,485
Everyone, let’s continue rehearsal.

389
00:24:26,485 --> 00:24:30,059
Let’s work on the show

390
00:24:30,377 --> 00:24:31,895
for the next performance.

391
00:24:32,077 --> 00:24:34,094
Come on, keep practicing, it’s nothing.

392
00:24:34,094 --> 00:24:35,366
Don’t overthink it.

393
00:24:35,366 --> 00:24:39,166
Keep the same rhythm—the “serng” beat,
just slow it down.

394
00:24:44,666 --> 00:24:45,427
Try doing it yourself
so you’ll know what the pressure feels like.

395
00:24:45,427 --> 00:24:46,023
I’m really worn out these days.

396
00:24:46,023 --> 00:24:46,796
You’re making everyone uncomfortable.

397
00:24:46,796 --> 00:24:47,296
P’Phet…

398
00:24:47,296 --> 00:24:48,154
Comment: Why so extreme?
Isn’t that overdoing it?

399
00:24:48,154 --> 00:24:49,198
Have you noticed?

400
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:51,644
Lately,

401
00:24:52,962 --> 00:24:55,059
our place has gotten really quiet.

402
00:25:01,066 --> 00:25:02,450
I feel it too.

403
00:25:04,177 --> 00:25:06,208
Back then, in the evenings like this,

404
00:25:06,753 --> 00:25:10,822
everyone would sit here, talk, and laugh together.

405
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:15,175
But now, everyone just goes to their own rooms.

406
00:25:16,084 --> 00:25:18,073
It’s like waiting to clock out.

407
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,400
It doesn’t feel like home anymore.

408
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:27,900
It feels more like a company chasing targets.

409
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:32,066
I know it’s not the same.

410
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,700
But we chose this path, Ploy.

411
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:39,131
If we want the troupe to survive,

412
00:25:39,676 --> 00:25:41,087
we have to accept some changes.

413
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:44,592
I believe

414
00:25:44,956 --> 00:25:46,530
it’ll turn out okay.

415
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,523
Even if right now…

416
00:25:50,523 --> 00:25:51,915
it doesn’t feel the same.

417
00:25:56,600 --> 00:25:58,480
I hope it turns out well.

418
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,380
Because if it doesn’t,

419
00:26:02,153 --> 00:26:03,757
we might lose the whole troupe

420
00:26:05,866 --> 00:26:07,266
and ourselves along with it.

421
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:27,745
Before, we could eat whatever we wanted.

422
00:26:27,745 --> 00:26:30,283
Just tell P’Ploy Ying and she’d let us.

423
00:26:30,828 --> 00:26:33,945
Now it’s boxed meals—every meal is the same.

424
00:26:35,066 --> 00:26:35,932
Yes.

425
00:26:35,932 --> 00:26:38,287
And we have to finish within thirty minutes.

426
00:26:38,287 --> 00:26:42,064
It feels less like family
but more like company employees.

427
00:26:42,746 --> 00:26:44,872
The Petchprakai Troupe used to be full of laughter.

428
00:26:45,327 --> 00:26:47,794
Now it’s just rules—nothing but rules.

429
00:26:48,266 --> 00:26:49,366
I feel the same.

430
00:26:52,266 --> 00:26:53,766
This place doesn’t feel like home anymore.

431
00:27:04,133 --> 00:27:04,749
Yeah, P’.

432
00:27:05,113 --> 00:27:07,268
The Petchprakai job—350,000.

433
00:27:08,132 --> 00:27:10,430
It’s confirmed for next month, right?

434
00:27:10,766 --> 00:27:14,266
Yes, I’ll sort it out with the troupe.

435
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:17,062
About the actors’ photos,

436
00:27:17,062 --> 00:27:19,751
you want to add more? No problem.

437
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,015
As for the extra amount,

438
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:24,333
I’ll settle it soon.

439
00:27:25,066 --> 00:27:25,600
Okay.

440
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:28,600
Just please don’t tell anyone yet.

441
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,200
Alright.

442
00:27:30,933 --> 00:27:31,900
Thank you very much.

443
00:27:41,900 --> 00:27:42,766
Three hundred fifty thousand…

444
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:47,333
Why did he tell P’Phet it was only 300,000?

445
00:27:48,133 --> 00:27:49,400
That’s a fifty-thousand difference.

446
00:27:50,166 --> 00:27:50,966
Damn.

447
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,900
That’s clearly cheating.

448
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,656
This job should be a hit.

449
00:27:56,656 --> 00:27:58,864
We got another sponsor.

450
00:27:58,864 --> 00:28:01,166
I’ll handle the details with the client.

451
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:03,359
P’Phet, P’Ploy—

452
00:28:05,495 --> 00:28:06,605
I need to say something.

453
00:28:07,014 --> 00:28:08,084
Right here, in front of Mr. Tohr.

454
00:28:11,400 --> 00:28:12,494
What is it, Pleng?

455
00:28:12,949 --> 00:28:14,666
Why are you talking so loud?

456
00:28:14,866 --> 00:28:16,610
The job Mr. Tohr just took—

457
00:28:17,292 --> 00:28:19,018
he got it for 350,000.

458
00:28:19,018 --> 00:28:20,969
So why tell P’Phet it’s only 300,000?

459
00:28:20,969 --> 00:28:24,572
The extra fifty, you kept it yourself.

460
00:28:24,572 --> 00:28:26,815
Isn’t that cheating?

461
00:28:27,266 --> 00:28:31,063
Pleng, what you said is partly true.

462
00:28:31,882 --> 00:28:34,129
The job itself is 300,000.

463
00:28:34,947 --> 00:28:36,206
But the extra fifty thousand

464
00:28:36,797 --> 00:28:38,816
is an add-on package from the client,

465
00:28:38,816 --> 00:28:40,266
for taking actor photos beforehand.

466
00:28:40,500 --> 00:28:41,968
Then why didn’t you say so from the start?

467
00:28:41,968 --> 00:28:43,392
Why hide it?

468
00:28:43,392 --> 00:28:44,333
Why let me find out myself?

469
00:28:44,733 --> 00:28:46,066
Because it just came up.

470
00:28:46,966 --> 00:28:49,400
No one had proposed anything like this before.

471
00:28:49,533 --> 00:28:50,878
This is the first time.

472
00:28:50,878 --> 00:28:51,378
Sigh…

473
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,133
What is this?

474
00:28:52,133 --> 00:28:53,300
I haven’t even explained yet,

475
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,533
and you’re already accusing me.

476
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:56,800
Pleng—

477
00:28:57,366 --> 00:28:59,766
Mr. Tohr might not actually be cheating us.

478
00:29:00,666 --> 00:29:01,466
Calm down.

479
00:29:01,766 --> 00:29:03,466
Let him explain first.

480
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:05,466
Why, P’?

481
00:29:06,866 --> 00:29:08,300
Every time I say something,

482
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:10,600
why do you never believe me?

483
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,866
Am I not important enough?

484
00:29:38,700 --> 00:29:41,609
You used to be my whole world.

485
00:29:44,746 --> 00:29:45,747
But today,

486
00:29:48,474 --> 00:29:50,000
not one of you believes me.

487
00:30:36,366 --> 00:30:37,166
P’Phet—

488
00:30:39,200 --> 00:30:40,533
If I’m really wrong,

489
00:30:42,066 --> 00:30:43,300
then prove it.

490
00:30:46,333 --> 00:30:47,666
If I’m telling the truth,

491
00:30:50,933 --> 00:30:52,144
one day,

492
00:30:53,190 --> 00:30:54,303
you’ll understand.

493
00:31:04,266 --> 00:31:05,066
Pleng—

494
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:06,800
Pleng!

495
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,066
Wait for me!

496
00:31:10,366 --> 00:31:11,166
Don’t go yet!

497
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:16,500
P’Ploy—

498
00:31:18,100 --> 00:31:19,666
I love this place like home.

499
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:23,000
But if no one trusts me here,

500
00:31:23,966 --> 00:31:25,266
then it’s not home anymore.

501
00:31:26,133 --> 00:31:27,400
Pleng, listen to me first.

502
00:31:30,866 --> 00:31:32,100
Don’t worry about me.

503
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:34,966
I can take care of myself.

504
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:42,608
This time,

505
00:31:44,108 --> 00:31:45,618
let me go my own way.

506
00:32:20,800 --> 00:32:21,560
Pleng—

507
00:32:21,878 --> 00:32:23,651
wait for me!

508
00:33:10,866 --> 00:33:11,865
Pleng!

509
00:33:12,911 --> 00:33:14,810
It’s so late—why are you calling?

510
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:18,600
Guy…

511
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:22,100
I…

512
00:33:25,066 --> 00:33:26,566
I just left home.

513
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:28,782
And…

514
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:31,311
I don’t know where to go.

515
00:33:33,966 --> 00:33:34,756
Are you…

516
00:33:35,711 --> 00:33:36,646
okay?

517
00:33:41,533 --> 00:33:42,700
Not really.

518
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:47,800
Come to me, I’ll send you the location.

519
00:33:52,100 --> 00:33:52,900
Okay.

520
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:55,766
Thanks, man.

521
00:34:31,066 --> 00:34:32,400
Are you okay, Pleng?

522
00:34:38,133 --> 00:34:40,000
Make yourself at home.

523
00:34:40,186 --> 00:34:41,399
Don’t worry about me.

524
00:34:42,217 --> 00:34:44,054
This place isn’t big,

525
00:34:44,327 --> 00:34:45,797
but there’s always room for you.

526
00:34:48,700 --> 00:34:49,200
So?

527
00:34:50,473 --> 00:34:51,506
Thank you so much.

528
00:35:02,133 --> 00:35:02,933
Pleng—

529
00:35:05,866 --> 00:35:07,666
If you don’t want to talk, that’s fine.

530
00:35:09,066 --> 00:35:10,366
But if you need to vent,

531
00:35:11,266 --> 00:35:12,566
I’m always here to listen.

532
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:20,333
You’ve grown up, huh.

533
00:35:21,766 --> 00:35:24,100
Waiting alone at night to come to Bangkok.

534
00:35:24,700 --> 00:35:25,468
Back then,

535
00:35:25,923 --> 00:35:28,219
you’d freak out over a blackout.

536
00:35:29,766 --> 00:35:31,366
I’m still scared of ghosts,

537
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,547
but now I’m more scared of reality.

538
00:35:36,547 --> 00:35:37,436
Listen to me.

539
00:35:38,482 --> 00:35:39,620
Ping, Pong, and Chae

540
00:35:40,211 --> 00:35:41,949
stole P’Phet’s valuables

541
00:35:42,404 --> 00:35:43,511
and ran away.

542
00:35:44,056 --> 00:35:45,462
P’Phet won’t press charges.

543
00:35:46,144 --> 00:35:46,980
He said

544
00:35:47,571 --> 00:35:49,304
they might have their reasons.

545
00:35:50,759 --> 00:35:51,769
And then

546
00:35:52,133 --> 00:35:53,376
there’s Mr. Tohr.

547
00:35:53,376 --> 00:35:54,897
Remember him?

548
00:35:55,442 --> 00:35:56,495
Yeah.

549
00:35:57,813 --> 00:35:59,095
At first, everyone was happy

550
00:35:59,095 --> 00:36:01,555
that he came to help.

551
00:36:02,466 --> 00:36:05,400
But I heard it loud and clear—

552
00:36:05,766 --> 00:36:07,533
he closed a deal for 350,000.

553
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:09,600
But told P’Phet it was only 300,000.

554
00:36:10,133 --> 00:36:11,859
When I found out and told them,

555
00:36:12,086 --> 00:36:15,559
He said that extra fifty thousand
was just his commission

556
00:36:15,559 --> 00:36:16,713
for landing the job.

557
00:36:17,077 --> 00:36:18,606
Whatever that is.

558
00:36:19,333 --> 00:36:20,133
Damn.

559
00:36:21,500 --> 00:36:23,245
This is serious, Pleng.

560
00:36:23,927 --> 00:36:25,266
What did P’Phet and P’Ploy say?

561
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:26,831
What do you think?

562
00:36:27,286 --> 00:36:28,379
They didn’t believe me.

563
00:36:28,652 --> 00:36:30,943
They believe everyone but me.

564
00:36:42,966 --> 00:36:43,973
Then

565
00:36:44,973 --> 00:36:46,779
you don’t have to prove it to them.

566
00:36:47,234 --> 00:36:48,812
Just make sure you know

567
00:36:49,630 --> 00:36:51,009
that you’re telling the truth.

568
00:37:09,484 --> 00:37:09,984
Come on.

569
00:37:10,529 --> 00:37:11,484
Let’s go upstairs.

570
00:37:17,500 --> 00:37:18,400
Sorry to bother you.

571
00:37:52,966 --> 00:37:53,766
P’Phet…

572
00:37:55,766 --> 00:37:57,600
I didn’t want to do this.

573
00:38:00,066 --> 00:38:02,400
I just wanted you to trust me once.

574
00:38:27,666 --> 00:38:28,340
It’s late.

575
00:38:28,749 --> 00:38:30,000
You’re still awake?

576
00:38:31,366 --> 00:38:32,466
Not really sleepy.

577
00:38:48,933 --> 00:38:49,733
Gross.

578
00:38:50,333 --> 00:38:51,500
It’s all messy.

579
00:38:54,700 --> 00:38:55,500
Hey—

580
00:38:57,466 --> 00:38:58,500
This Game Boy—

581
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:01,466
you still kept it?

582
00:39:02,933 --> 00:39:03,733
Damn.

583
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:06,666
P’Phet gave this to us when we were kids.

584
00:39:08,466 --> 00:39:09,500
I still remember.

585
00:39:09,933 --> 00:39:12,000
We fought over it until it almost broke.

586
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:16,791
Come here.

587
00:39:17,927 --> 00:39:20,701
Back then, believe it or not,

588
00:39:21,428 --> 00:39:22,990
I never beat him.

589
00:39:24,217 --> 00:39:26,989
That’s why I got into gaming.

590
00:39:26,989 --> 00:39:28,104
And

591
00:39:28,104 --> 00:39:30,419
why I still want to stream games.

592
00:39:34,500 --> 00:39:35,300
Pleng—

593
00:39:37,200 --> 00:39:38,600
no matter what path you choose,

594
00:39:39,500 --> 00:39:40,733
don’t forget

595
00:39:43,666 --> 00:39:45,000
you’re not alone.

596
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:51,866
Yeah, thanks.

597
00:39:53,766 --> 00:39:54,666
By the way,

598
00:39:56,733 --> 00:39:57,800
you and that person—

599
00:39:58,666 --> 00:39:59,500
how far have you gotten?

600
00:40:00,466 --> 00:40:01,563
Tell me.

601
00:40:01,563 --> 00:40:02,066
What?

602
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:05,634
How did this become about me?

603
00:40:05,634 --> 00:40:06,427
Hey—

604
00:40:06,427 --> 00:40:07,266
I just want to know.

605
00:40:07,666 --> 00:40:08,466
Tell me.

606
00:40:08,500 --> 00:40:09,666
Give me an update, come on.

607
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:10,600
Hey—

608
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:11,500
Just a bit.

609
00:40:12,766 --> 00:40:13,420
Nothing.

610
00:40:13,420 --> 00:40:13,920
Alright.

611
00:40:14,300 --> 00:40:14,968
I’m going to sleep.

612
00:40:14,968 --> 00:40:15,566
Okay.

613
00:40:16,933 --> 00:40:17,800
You’re not telling me?

614
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,130
No, it’s not that—

615
00:40:37,130 --> 00:40:39,490
I told you before, you just don’t remember.

616
00:40:39,490 --> 00:40:41,266
Wait, let me try again.

617
00:40:45,133 --> 00:40:46,400
Thank you very much.

618
00:40:47,733 --> 00:40:48,533
Thank you.

619
00:41:01,533 --> 00:41:03,521
What are you doing? Why so slow?

620
00:41:04,248 --> 00:41:07,457
You have fifteen minutes—finish and go rehearse.

621
00:41:08,048 --> 00:41:09,220
Understood?

622
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:15,716
Clean this up already—I’ve seen it since yesterday.

623
00:41:15,716 --> 00:41:18,395
Why leave it for days?

624
00:41:18,395 --> 00:41:21,566
What were those three told to do?

625
00:41:21,900 --> 00:41:23,933
Yes, this is Petchprakai Troupe.

626
00:41:24,533 --> 00:41:26,733
A job? How much is it?

627
00:41:27,066 --> 00:41:28,239
Yes, that works.

628
00:41:28,239 --> 00:41:28,739
Stop, stop.

629
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:31,796
The rhythm’s off—don’t rush the drums.

630
00:41:31,796 --> 00:41:32,500
Let’s do it again.

631
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:38,533
How many times do I have to say this?

632
00:41:38,966 --> 00:41:39,966
What is this?

633
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:41,166
Why keep this?

634
00:41:41,700 --> 00:41:42,900
To worship it?

635
00:41:43,300 --> 00:41:44,100
Even a knife.

636
00:42:16,500 --> 00:42:19,300
These aren’t expensive things,

637
00:42:19,933 --> 00:42:21,372
but every piece,

638
00:42:21,372 --> 00:42:23,766
comes from Father and Mother’s hard work.

639
00:42:26,266 --> 00:42:29,141
They remind us that our family

640
00:42:29,141 --> 00:42:30,675
is still together.

641
00:42:31,948 --> 00:42:32,761
Phet…

642
00:42:34,534 --> 00:42:35,978
I want you to remember this,

643
00:42:36,751 --> 00:42:38,770
our family stands

644
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:41,361
because we help each other.

645
00:42:43,498 --> 00:42:47,122
One day,
you’ll lead the Petchprakai Troupe

646
00:42:47,622 --> 00:42:49,049
forward.

647
00:42:49,458 --> 00:42:52,629
Not because I say so or because you’re the eldest,

648
00:42:54,993 --> 00:42:56,219
but because you

649
00:42:58,401 --> 00:42:59,821
are the heart of the troupe.

650
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:08,783
I promise,

651
00:43:11,283 --> 00:43:13,393
I’ll take care of our family the best I can.

652
00:43:29,723 --> 00:43:34,234
No matter how hard it gets,
they’ll always be my home.

653
00:43:58,163 --> 00:44:00,763
♪ Everything changes ♪

654
00:44:01,305 --> 00:44:05,484
♪ Hearts change too ♪

655
00:44:06,211 --> 00:44:09,751
♪ We begin to lose strength ♪

656
00:44:10,342 --> 00:44:12,496
♪ Growing weary ♪

657
00:44:13,405 --> 00:44:15,587
♪ We will rise and fight ♪

658
00:44:16,132 --> 00:44:19,391
♪ Believe me, my child ♪

659
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,349
♪ As time goes by ♪

660
00:44:23,167 --> 00:44:25,206
♪ It passes on ♪

661
00:44:26,070 --> 00:44:28,612
♪ Hold on to memories ♪

662
00:44:29,112 --> 00:44:32,503
♪ Remind the heart ♪

663
00:44:33,685 --> 00:44:37,749
♪ I will make it happen ♪

664
00:44:38,476 --> 00:44:42,140
♪ One day ♪

665
00:44:58,133 --> 00:44:59,572
I have good news.

666
00:44:59,572 --> 00:45:02,800
This year, our village fair is coming back.

667
00:45:03,266 --> 00:45:04,566
Honestly,

668
00:45:04,566 --> 00:45:06,447
I think the issue between you and Guy

669
00:45:06,447 --> 00:45:08,868
has been weighing on you for a long time.

670
00:45:08,868 --> 00:45:10,900
What did you gain from being mad at your family?

671
00:45:12,466 --> 00:45:13,400
I miss home.

672
00:45:14,100 --> 00:45:15,557
Fight on with me.

673
00:45:15,557 --> 00:45:16,936
Ploy…

674
00:45:16,936 --> 00:45:18,533
Fighting alone is lonely.

675
00:45:21,266 --> 00:45:22,066
Yeah.
